45.62	Eric_Ripert	Eric Ripert	Eric Ripert (rih-pair') (born 1965 in Antibes) is a French chef, author and television personality specializing in modern French cuisine and renowned for his work with seafood. His flagship restaurant, Le Bernardin, located in New York City, is routinely ranked among the best restaurants in the world by Restaurant magazine's and S. Pellegrino's annual "Worlds 50 Best Restaurants" list and holds the maximum ratings of four stars from The New York Times and three stars from the Michelin Guide. Ripert inherited the title of executive chef and partner of Le Bernardin from founding chef Gilbert Le Coze, who opened the restaurant with his sister Maguy Le Coze in 1972.	
